  <original-body>With the i18n support of rails, you may translate the attributes of a model like this:

@@@ ruby
en:
  activerecord:
    attributes:
      user:
        name: User name
        email: Email address
@@@

But if you use
@@@ ruby
form_for @user do |f|
  f.label :user
  f.text_field :user
end
@@@
rails will print out &quot;User&quot; instead of &quot;User name&quot;</original-body>
